François Cluzet https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fran%C3%A7ois_Cluzet 0 François Cluzet (born 21 September 1955) is a French film and theatre actor. In 2007, Cluzet won a French César Award after starring as a doctor suspected of double homicide in thriller Tell No One (original title Ne le dis à personne). Cluzet may be best known for his role as Philippe in the international hit film The Intouchables (2011). François_Cluzet ( born 21_September_1955 ) is a_French_film_and_theatre_actor .
